RCW 51.14.340

Ombuds office—Powers and duties.

The office of the ombuds shall have the following powers and duties:(1) To act as an advocate for injured workers of self-insured employers;(2) To offer and provide information on industrial insurance as appropriate to workers of self-insured employers;(3) To identify, investigate, and facilitate resolution of industrial insurance complaints from workers of self-insured employers;(4) To maintain a statewide toll-free telephone number for the receipt of complaints and inquiries; and(5) To refer complaints to the department when appropriate.

The office of the ombuds shall have the following powers and duties:

(1) To act as an advocate for injured workers of self-insured employers;

(2) To offer and provide information on industrial insurance as appropriate to workers of self-insured employers;

(3) To identify, investigate, and facilitate resolution of industrial insurance complaints from workers of self-insured employers;

(4) To maintain a statewide toll-free telephone number for the receipt of complaints and inquiries; and

(5) To refer complaints to the department when appropriate.

[ 2013 c 23 s 109; 2007 c 281 s 5.]
